<subSubSection id="D1354B07AD4E51328F1017E96052D111" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C04755BBE7E607137AA2F1B51F5E640C" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B10B665B1CE50F25EBDDEC6279B0B445" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: South Pirin Mt., Kalimantsi vill., 06.04.-10.05.2002, pitfall traps, 1 w.; same place, 06.08-08.09.2002, pitfall traps, 1 w., leg. M. Langourov; Struma Valley, Kamenitsa vill., 23.06-08.08.2002, pitfall traps, 1 w., leg. D. Chobanov. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="EB6055D8B0EB99044E0D8B0E1D6898EF" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="166DC31BD444AF737E540E3F3CB3CF26" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="CBEABB0A59E20927D1B8287CFEF1AEB8" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B31A1B18C58AC0CF5312120680CBEFAE" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
First record for Bulgaria. A rarely collected ant that is a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="21AC430EDA9BC5EE86AA2B41A3A53C99" authority="Mayr, 1861" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="Forel" baseAuthorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Temnothorax graecus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="graecus">
<emphasis id="321E0F8FDF64C5E13929FDEF0C14A82D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Temnothorax graecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (
<bibRefCitation id="AC6C59FA3485F5D0D49BF4AD20806564" author="Salata, S." journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="81 - 131" refId="B7725952" refString="Salata, S., Borowiec, L., 2019. Preliminary division of not socially parasitic Greek Temnothorax Mayr, 1861 (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) with a description of three new species. ZooKeys 87: 81 - 131" title="Preliminary division of not socially parasitic Greek Temnothorax Mayr, 1861 (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) with a description of three new species" volume="87" year="2019">Salata and Borowiec 2019b</bibRefCitation>
). This species is known from Turkey, its type locality, as well as from Israel and the Greek islands (
<bibRefCitation id="0A664144DDBC0835B100822B03C4F855" author="Borowiec, L." journalOrPublisher="Genus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="461 - 563" refId="B7725651" refString="Borowiec, L., Salata, S., 2012. Ants of Greece - checklist, comments and new faunistic data (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Genus 23 (4): 461 - 563" title="Ants of Greece - checklist, comments and new faunistic data (Hymenoptera: Formicidae)" volume="23" year="2012">Borowiec and Salata 2012</bibRefCitation>
). It was recently recorded in Greek Thrace (
<bibRefCitation id="B55C4E4D4111994322660706E58CC9CB" author="Bracko, G." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7725696" refString="Bracko, G., Kiran, K., Karaman, C., Salata, S., Borowiec, L., 2016. Survey of the ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of the Greek Thrace. Biodiversity Data Journal 4 (7945)" title="Survey of the ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of the Greek Thrace" volume="4" year="2016">
<normalizedToken id="3E8E2BD519722A50DE91918FA2820725" originalValue="Bračko">Bracko</normalizedToken>
et al. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
